Uses of Package
suncertify.db

Packages that use suncertify.db
suncertify.db Contains Framework and API to access database files data and structure localy or remotly. 
suncertify.db.impl Contains an implementation for an EngineService 
suncertify.db.server Contains the database engine network server framework and API. 
suncertify.db.server.rmi Contains an implementation for engine network server using RMI. 
suncertify.model.db Modeling for contractors information exists in a database file is performed by this package classes. 
 

Classes in suncertify.db used by suncertify.db
Data.RecordsHandler
          Defines the strategy for database file records bytes read/write operations to be used by an instance of Data.
Data.RecordsLockHandler
          Defines the strategy for records locking behavior to be used by an instance of Data.
DBMain
          Define an interface for database file records create, read, lock, update and delete operations.
DuplicateKeyException
          Thrown to indicate a duplicate key constraint has been broken while inserting a record in database file.
Engine
          Defines an engine for managing the access to a single database file data through sessions.
EngineService
          Defines a service for creating DB engines for local database files, references for remote DB engines, and engines network services.
EngineServiceException
          Thrown to indicate a failure in EngineService operations.
RecordNotFoundException
          An indicator if a record to be read, updated, or deleted is not found in file or already deleted.
Schema
          A descriptor for a database file record structure.
Session
          Defines a unique access to a database file engine.
